# Design System: Layout & Animation

> **Scope**: Applies to page-level components and feature components. Governs section structure, grid layouts, animations, and responsive behavior.
> **Full spec**: `docs/design-system/layout.md`

## Section Structure

Every major section follows this pattern:

```tsx
<section className="py-32">
  <div className="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6">
    {/* 1. Section label badge */}
    <div className="mb-8 inline-flex items-center gap-3 rounded-full border border-[var(--accent)]/30 bg-[var(--accent)]/5 px-5 py-2">
      <span className="h-2 w-2 rounded-full bg-[var(--accent)]" />
      <span className="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-[var(--accent)]">
        Section Name
      </span>
    </div>

    {/* 2. Headline — key word gets gradient text */}
    <h2 className="font-display text-4xl leading-tight tracking-tight md:text-[3.25rem]">
      Headline with <span className="gradient-text">highlight</span>
    </h2>

    {/* 3. Content grid */}
    <div className="mt-16 grid grid-cols-1 gap-6 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
      {/* Cards */}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
```

## Grid Patterns

| Layout | Grid | Usage |
|:-------|:-----|:------|
| Hero | `grid-cols-[1.1fr_0.9fr]` | Asymmetric text + graphic |
| Features | `grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3` | Responsive card grid |
| Stats | `grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4` | Metric cards |

## Inverted Sections

For dramatic contrast, flip the palette:

```tsx
<section className="bg-[var(--foreground)] text-[var(--background)]">
  <div className="relative">
    <div className="absolute inset-0 opacity-[0.03]" style={{
      backgroundImage: 'radial-gradient(circle, currentColor 1px, transparent 1px)',
      backgroundSize: '32px 32px'
    }} />
    {/* Content with relative z-index */}
  </div>
</section>
```

## Radial Glow Decorations

Place at section corners for ambient warmth:

```tsx
<div className="pointer-events-none absolute -top-32 left-1/2 h-[500px] w-[500px] -translate-x-1/2 rounded-full bg-[var(--accent)] opacity-[0.03] blur-[150px]" />
```

## Animation Rules

### Entrance Animations (Framer Motion)

```typescript
const easeOut = [0.16, 1, 0.3, 1] as const;

const fadeInUp = {
  hidden: { opacity: 0, y: 28 },
  visible: { opacity: 1, y: 0, transition: { duration: 0.7, ease: easeOut } }
};

const stagger = {
  hidden: {},
  visible: { transition: { staggerChildren: 0.1, delayChildren: 0.1 } }
};
```

Viewport: `{ once: true, amount: 0.15, margin: "-60px" }`

### Transition Defaults

| Context | Duration | Class |
|:--------|:---------|:------|
| Standard | `200ms` | `transition-all duration-200` |
| Hover lift | `300ms` | `transition-all duration-300` |
| Entrance | `700ms` | Framer Motion `duration: 0.7` |

### Continuous Animations

- Pulsing dot: `animate-pulse` or custom `2s` keyframe
- Floating elements: `4-5s` ease-in-out, ±10px y-axis
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`

## Responsive Rules

- Mobile first: single column, full-width buttons (`w-full sm:w-auto`)
- Headlines scale: `text-[2.75rem]` → `text-6xl` → `text-[5.25rem]`
- Section padding: `py-28` → `py-44`
- Hide decorative elements on mobile: `hidden lg:block`
- Touch targets: 44px minimum on all interactive elements

## Desktop App Rules

> **This is a Tauri desktop app, not a website.** Desktop-specific constraints apply.
> **Full spec**: `docs/design-system/layout.md` → "Desktop App Layout Principles"

### Panel Layout

- Sidebar and main content MUST use `react-resizable-panels` (shadcn `Resizable`) for drag-to-resize
- Sidebar: `minSize={20}` (240px), `maxSize={35}` (400px), `defaultSize={25}` (256px)
- Collapsed sidebar: `64px` icon-only mode
- Persist sidebar width via `autoSaveId` in localStorage
- At `<768px`, sidebar becomes a Sheet drawer (not resizable)

### Component Placement

| Region | Behavior |
|:-------|:---------|
| Sidebar | Fixed width, full height, always visible |
| Main content | Flexible, fills remaining space, scrolls internally |
| Primary actions | Top-right of content area or top of sidebar |
| Navigation | Left sidebar only, never buried in dropdowns |

### Resize Behavior

- No hardcoded pixel widths on layout containers — use `flex`, `grid`, or panel constraints
- Debounce resize handlers (150ms or `requestAnimationFrame`)
- Content should show MORE as window grows (more columns, more rows), not just stretch
- Text content: cap line width at ~65 characters for readability
- `transition-all duration-300` on layout shifts (sidebar collapse/expand)

### Window Constraints

- Minimum window size: `900×600` (set in `tauri.conf.json`)
- Default window size: `1100×700` (not maximized)
- Never open maximized by default
- Save/restore window size and position across sessions

### Keyboard Shortcuts

Desktop users expect keyboard shortcuts. Register globally:

| Action | Shortcut |
|:-------|:---------|
| New meeting | `Cmd/Ctrl+N` |
| Search | `Cmd/Ctrl+K` |
| Toggle sidebar | `Cmd/Ctrl+B` |
| Settings | `Cmd/Ctrl+,` |
| Close/Cancel | `Escape` |

## DO NOT

- Use hardcoded color values — always use `var(--token)`
- Center everything — embrace strategic asymmetry
- Use flat backgrounds everywhere — use inverted sections and gradient glows
- Skip animations — the design should feel alive
- Use `text-black` or `text-white` — use `var(--foreground)` and `var(--background)`
- Use fixed pixel widths for main layout — use flex/grid/panels
- Use `transform: translate` for sidebar sliding — use panel library or `margin`
- Open window maximized — choose a useful default size
- Let panels resize below minimum usable size
